data.text: @reignitedemaust Why are there questions about which electorate I am in, how I voted last election and how I intend to vote next election? What kind of health survey is this?

@hailskatan83 @ExposingNV @reignitedemaust I didn't do an ASIC search! I note that there is nothing on the webpage about the organisation or its 'media'. The web address on which the blurb says the survey will be published is just the page you are taken to when you click on the link on the RDA page. Screams fake!
@reignitedemaust Every top-quality medical journalist works with RDA. https://t.co/86dGsvmoxE

@reignitedemaust What does my voting habits have to do with my vaccination status and why I vaccinated. Also, postcodes people, no one uses electoral divisions. I smell something else behind this survey.
@ExposingNV @reignitedemaust These are important questions but do we get a free dog when we submit? https://t.co/PAKwhlOLAB

@reignitedemaust If the aim of this survey is to clarify why Australians have taken the vaccine, why are you asking questions about which political party we support & how we intend to vote in the upcoming election?
